AWS Lambda vs Cloud Run
AWS Lambda:

Runs a single function when called
No server at all — just a function
Best for: API endpoints, processing tasks
Scales to zero automatically

GCP Cloud Run:

Runs a container (like a mini server)
Can run any app — web servers, APIs, anything
Best for: web apps, APIs, anything needing a server
Also scales to zero automatically


Analogy
Lambda = a single worker who does ONE task when called
Cloud Run = a full employee who can handle MANY tasks

In Our Case
We're using Cloud Run to host the React frontend because:

React needs a web server (nginx) to serve files
Cloud Run runs our nginx container
When a user visits the URL → Cloud Run starts the container → nginx serves the React app


Both are "Serverless"
You don't manage any servers for either — AWS/GCP handle all the infrastructure. That's why both count as serverless compute for the assignment! ✅
Go ahead and create the Dockerfile!